name: Anthony Walker
bio: As President of ABG, I work alongside an incredible team to bridge AI, business, and engineering to create real world solutions. Together, we focus on projects that make a meaningful impact, and if AI ever takes over, at least we trained it well.

name: Noah Feigenbaum
bio: As VP of Operations, I oversee all internal procedures, working alongside an incredible team to streamline the production of AI solutions for real world problems.

name: Jahzarah McIntosh
bio: I lead the educational initiatives as Vice President of Education, where I design and facilitate our New Member Education (NME) program. I am dedicated to making sure members have access to curated resources, foundational training, and skills aligned with real-world applications.

name: Evelyn Chao
bio: As VP External, I manage relations with ABG's project clientele, spearhead the direction of internal projects, and direct ABG's AI Internship Program.

name: Michael Todaro
bio: As Vice President of Marketing for ABG, I’m responsible for building and maintaining the club’s brand identity. This includes managing our social media strategy to engage and grow our audience, designing custom merchandise that reflects our mission and culture, and developing the visual direction of the club to ensure a consistent and compelling aesthetic across all platforms.

name: Jacob Walker
bio: I am a junior at the University of Michigan studying Economics and Physics, serving as Vice President of Sponsorship for the AI Business Group. In this role I focus on building strategic partnerships that support our club's goals and objectives.

name: Jessica Au
bio: As Co-Vice President of Recruitment at ABG, I work to attract new members by highlighting the unique opportunities and projects our club provides. We focus on highlighting AI’s potential to new members and how ABG can all impact our world today. If you can’t beat AI, join the club.

name: John Fullerton
bio: As Co-VP of Finance, I am responsible for ensuring the monetary health of our club. I work with my partner, Vincent, to responsibly raise and distribute funds to promote the growth and success of ABG. We are 37 trillion dollars better off than the US government.

name: Robert Doyle
bio: As VP of Social for AI Business Group, I design and execute events that foster connection across the Ross School of Business, College of Engineering, and broader U of M community. I also build partnerships with local businesses and lead initiatives that strengthen member engagement and club culture.

name: Vincent Antonio
bio: As Co-VP of Finance, I help oversee the financial health of ABG by managing budgets, allocating resources for projects and events, and identifying funding opportunities that support our mission to bridge AI and business. I work alongside John to ensure our club remains on a strong financial footing, empowering members to build real-world AI solutions that drive meaningful impact.

name: Ethan Watson
bio: As Co-Vice President of Recruitment at ABG, I work to attract new members while showcasing the unique opportunities, community, and resources our club offers. Together, we focus on new members who are interested in AI and its effects in the world today. AI won't take your job, but the person using AI might.
